leads.lead_text: Nut lenticular or unequally trigonous with the dorsal angle obtuse, surface always shining; style 2- or 3-fid
Nut equally trigonous, with the dorsal angle acute, pale yellow or grey and dull to blackish and shining; style 3-fid
Nut lenticular, straw-coloured to dark golden brown, the surface minutely but obviously reticulate; style 2-fid
Nut plano-convex or trigonous, dark red-brown to black, the surface not obviously reticulate; style 2- or 3-fid
